THE END OF THE WORLD | SHORT FILM | RAINDANCE FILM SCHOOL 

** CASTING CALL  - UNPAID -  EXPENSES ONLY *

*We are looking to gain funding to be able to pay everyone should this be the case you will be paid for your participation. *

**SHOOT DATES: **20TH, 21ST & 22ND MARCH 

***ACTORS MUST BE LONDON BASED* **

**SYNOPSIS: **

**THE END OF THE WORLD **follows a 20 - something immigrant student struggling with bad grades, an unreachable crush, and the pressure to define her future. While everyone else seems to know who she should be, she feels lost - until the sudden outbreak of a global pandemic disrupts everything, giving her an unexpected chance to rethink her life and what truly matters. 

**CHARACTERS: **

Norma (23, Native Italian) 

Luca (23, Native Italian) 

Lisa (22, Any Ethnicity) 

Jess (20, Any Ethnicity) 

Please refer to the google drive link where you will find folders related to the above characters.

[https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1xzjn4r_ktLoy3f7lUUIMVlbdyVdS1mUc?usp=sharing](https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1xzjn4r_ktLoy3f7lUUIMVlbdyVdS1mUc?usp=sharing) 

Please click on the relevant folder for the character you will be auditioning for and submit your tape to us by FRIDAY 9TH JANUARY 2026. 

**TAPING INSTRUCTIONS:**

**Please reference your name, where you are based along with the character you are auditioning for at the beginning of your tape. **

Once completed please send your tape to Francesca Marago and Jasmin Batler to the following email: [theendoftheworldshort@gmail.com](mailto:theendoftheworldshort@gmail.com) and please put the CHARACTER you are auditioning for in the subject line along with your NAME. Please also attach a brief description of your experience a long with a link to your spotlight/acting profile/CV.

## **üé≠ CASTING CALL ‚Äî TALKING MIME (WHITEFACE)**

**Mini Sessions | Non-Union | Ages 35‚Äì45**

Hi everyone ‚Äî we‚Äôre **RETROcirq Studios, LLC**, a small, human-produced media studio creating short-form, nostalgia-inspired content for YouTube.

Our current project, **Studio 3**, is a curated channel inspired by classic late-night TV, UHF programming, and retro media. It‚Äôs designed to feel like something you *drop into* ‚Äî short segments, odd interstitials, and occasional performances.

**This is not a scripted series and not a cast-driven show.**

**üé≠ WHAT WE‚ÄôRE CASTING**

We‚Äôre looking for **one non-union female performer (ages 35‚Äì45)** for **short mini-sessions** as a **talking mime**.

These are brief on-camera appearances used as:

* bumpers
* short segments
* interstitial moments

Each appearance runs approximately **30‚Äì90 seconds**.

**üìå BOOKING, SCOPE & OUR COMMITMENT**

This role is booked **one session at a time**.

Any additional sessions, if offered, are determined later based on project needs and are **not guaranteed**.

**What we do promise:**

* Clear communication
* Fair compensation, paid on time
* Transparency about each booking
* No surprises or implied obligations

If additional sessions are offered, they will always be discussed openly and confirmed in advance.

**PERFORMANCE DETAILS**

* Light dialogue combined with expressive facial/physical performance
* Calm, grounded delivery (restraint over theatrics)
* Comfortable speaking directly to camera
* Comfortable working in a small, flexible production environment

üëâ **Mime experience is NOT required.**

Strong on-camera presence and facial expressiveness matter more than formal mime training.

**üé® MAKEUP REQUIREMENT**

* **Classic whiteface mime makeup**
   * Clean white base
   * Simple black accents (eyes, brows, mouth)
   * No prosthetics
   * No elaborate or theatrical designs

Whiteface is used strictly as **visual shorthand**, not character lore.

**‚ùå THIS IS NOT**

* A series lead
* A guaranteed recurring role
* A long-term commitment
* An influencer or branding opportunity

**üé¨ AUDITION**

* 30‚Äì60 second self-tape
* Neutral background
* Simple wardrobe
* **Whiteface makeup applied**
* One short prompt (shared privately)

**üíµ COMPENSATION**

* **$150 flat per session**
* Booked one session at a time
* Additional sessions not guaranteed

* **Non-union performers only**

RETROcirq Studios is intentionally small and human-first.

We value clarity, flexibility, respectful collaboration, and low drama.

If you‚Äôre looking for something lightweight, creative, and clearly defined ‚Äî with honest communication ‚Äî this may be a good fit.

Performer acknowledges that this project is **produced remotely**. Performer will record footage from their own location using their own equipment (smartphone or camera acceptable) following general technical guidelines provided by Producer. No travel, studio access, or in-person production is required or implied.

**Interested?**

Please comment **‚Äúinterested‚Äù** and **DM us** for audition details.

**Quick notes:**

‚Ä¢ $150 flat per session (not negotiable)

‚Ä¢ Non-union only

‚Ä¢ Ages 35‚Äì45

‚Ä¢ Whiteface makeup required

‚Ä¢ Booked one session at a time; additional sessions not guaranteed

‚Ä¢ We promise clear communication and fair pay for every session

Performer will record footage from their own location using their own equipment (smartphone or camera acceptable) following general technical guidelines provided by Producer. No travel, studio access, or in-person production is required or implied.

**Interested?**

**Quick notes:**

‚Ä¢ $150 flat per session (not negotiable)

‚Ä¢ Non-union only

‚Ä¢ Ages 35‚Äì45

‚Ä¢ Whiteface makeup required

‚Ä¢ Booked one session at a time; additional sessions not guaranteed

‚Ä¢ We promise clear communication and fair pay for every session

items.text:
Next month I'll hit a major milestone. I booked my first speaking role in a feature film four years ago from the producers of Taxi Driver and American History X, and that film, Where Sweet Dreams Die, premieres worldwide next month. four years ago, I was not sure if I would ever get a real break, but I kept going to auditions, kept training, kept showing up, and kept trying to get better.

If you are chasing this dream too, do not quit. The grind feels endless until the moment something finally clicks, and sometimes that moment shows up when you least expect it. Your breakthrough might be a lot closer than you think.

How Script Analysis Changes Everything About Your Auditions

Most auditions aren‚Äôt lost because of talent ‚Äî they‚Äôre lost because of uncertainty.

When actors don‚Äôt fully understand what their character wants, why they want it, or how they‚Äôre trying to get it, that confusion shows up instantly on camera. Lines feel disconnected. Emotional beats feel random. Choices feel hesitant instead of intentional. And casting directors stop watching.

This video breaks down how Script & Scene Analysis inside MyAuditionAI.com removes that uncertainty before the camera ever turns on.

items.text:
**CASTING CALL: THREE ACTOR-SINGERS FOR RECURRING MUSICAL COMEDY PROJECT **

**Project Title:** Standing On Shoulders 

**Production Company:** Independent 

**Casting Director:** Adam Scamvougeras 

**Union Status:** Non-Union 

**Compensation:** Credit & Footage Provided 

What if The Beatles were socially inept or The Monkees were morally corrupt? You get Standing On Shoulders! This project is an original musical comedy project that mixes narrative storytelling with humorous songs, performed by a recurring ensemble.

We are seeking three actor-singers to complete the four-person performance group.  

This particular project is acting-first. Actors should have strong comedic instincts and solid singing abilities. Instrumental ability is seen as a plus but not required. The music itself is created in collaboration with talented musicians from Vancouver and abroad.

While this project is ongoing, it is not a full-time commitment. Scheduling is flexible and performers will have plenty of time for other acting opportunities. This is a collaborative, passion-driven project designed to grow over time.

In 2026, we will be creating a few musical comedy videos. The long-term ambition with this project is to make albums or features starring the band. 

This is a recurring project for actors interested in returning to the same project over time. 

The available roles are as follows:

BAND MEMBER #1 (Male, mid-late 20s, open ethnicity) The ‚Äúsuave‚Äù one. His motivation for being part of the band is to meet girls. 

BAND MEMBER #2 (Male, mid-late 20s, open ethnicity) The ‚Äúpunk‚Äù one. His motivation for being part of the band is as a chance to rebel against the entertainment industry. 

BAND MEMBER #3 (Female, mid-late 20s, open ethnicity) The ‚Äúambitious‚Äù one. Her motivation for being part of the band is to get noticed. She sees the band as a stepping stone to better things and is always one foot out the door. 

For submissions, please submit a headshot, a resume (if available), and two short videos (30-60 seconds each): 

1) Singing sample

2) Acting sample for the role you're submitting for. It can be a brief monologue, a conversation with your friend, a self-written bit, etc. 

Please email to adamscamvougeras@gmail.com. Also, please include a brief message in the email explaining why you feel you‚Äôre right for the project and what interests you about it. 

Thank you so much for taking the time to consider my project, and I** **wish you all the happiest of holidays.

items.text:
## CASTING CALL ‚Äî AMBER (LEAD rOLE)

**Project: Short Film**

Genre: Psychological Drama / Tech Thriller

Shoot Location: Lower Mainland, BC

Shoot Dates: TBD

Compensation: Volunteer / Passion Project

**ROLE: AMBER**

Age Range: 27‚Äì40

Gender: Female

Ethnicity: Open / Race-agnostic

**CHARACTER SNAPSHOT**

Amber is a high-performing Director of Sales at a tech company. Outwardly confident and disciplined, she is internally restless and unable to feel content. She is addicted to the chase‚Äîalways moving forward, never celebrating wins.

When Amber gains access to an experimental technology, she relies on it too much. The technology destabilizes her judgment, blurring truth, error, and perception.

By the end, she withdraws from modern life‚Äînot in rebellion, but to preserve her sanity.

**PERFORMANCE NOTES**

This is a subtle, internal performance. We are seeking an actor who can convey psychological shifts through restraint, stillness, and micro-expression.

This is not a loud breakdown. Amber‚Äôs collapse is quiet, logical, and unsettling‚Äîdriven by over-certainty and loss of trust in her own judgment.

**KEY TRAITS**

Intelligent

Controlled

Ambitious (not arrogant)

Emotionally guarded

Increasingly detached

**AUDITION REQUIREMENTS**

Self-tape audition

One dramatic scene (sides to be provided)

**SUBMISSION DETAILS**

Please submit:

Headshot

Resume (if available)

Email submissions to: soultales.ca@gmail.com

Subject: AMBER ‚Äì Casting Submission

**NOTE!!!**

This is a serious passion project with a small, committed team. We are looking for actors who are reliable, prepared, and respectful of time and effort. Please apply only if you can fully commit to rehearsals, shoot days, and clear communication throughout the process. Consistency and follow-through are essential for this role.

This project is not suitable for flaky or tentative participation. If you are unsure about your availability or commitment, we kindly ask that you do not apply.

**ROLE: AMBER**

Age Range: 27‚Äì40

Gender: Female

Ethnicity: Open / Race-agnostic

**CHARACTER SNAPSHOT**

Amber is a high-performing Director of Sales at a tech company. Outwardly confident and disciplined, she is internally restless and unable to feel content. She is addicted to the chase‚Äîalways moving forward, never celebrating wins.

When Amber gains access to an experimental technology, she relies on it too much. The technology destabilizes her judgment, blurring truth, error, and perception.

By the end, she withdraws from modern life‚Äînot in rebellion, but to preserve her sanity.

**PERFORMANCE NOTES**

This is a subtle, internal performance. We are seeking an actor who can convey psychological shifts through restraint, stillness, and micro-expression.

This is not a loud breakdown. Amber‚Äôs collapse is quiet, logical, and unsettling‚Äîdriven by over-certainty and loss of trust in her own judgment.

**KEY TRAITS**

Intelligent

Controlled

Ambitious (not arrogant)

Emotionally guarded

Increasingly detached

**AUDITION REQUIREMENTS**

Self-tape audition

One dramatic scene (sides to be provided)

**SUBMISSION DETAILS**

Please submit:

Headshot

Resume (if available)

Email submissions to: soultales.ca@gmail.com

Subject: AMBER ‚Äì Casting Submission

**NOTE!!!**

This is a serious passion project with a small, committed team. We are looking for actors who are reliable, prepared, and respectful of time and effort. Please apply only if you can fully commit to rehearsals, shoot days, and clear communication throughout the process. Consistency and follow-through are essential for this role.

This project is not suitable for flaky or tentative participation. If you are unsure about your availability or commitment, we kindly ask that you do not apply.

items.text:
''They got me an apartment in New York!''

She was close to tears on our zoom call.

''And the flight's paid for too! I even get a per diem of $100 a day! 
That's on top of what they pay me and it's A LOT, KC!''

After she got over the thrill of booking a recurring role on a series (in NY!!!) her mind was blown about everything else that came with it. 

She'd put almost 5 years of constant study with me to get to this level and she took absolutely none of it for granted. 

It was a lot of work and the work didn't stop when she got to NY. 

18 hour days.
Incredibly challenging scenes (I wish I could tell you because it's mind-blowing what she did but I can't).
Living in a country where she knew no one.

An since that series she's continued to work hard and book. 

It doesn't get easier when you find success. The challenges are different. 

You can start now and put in the work and build the muscles that help you meet those challenges. 

Or you can look back in 5 years from now and think I wish I did it. 

Regret is an ugly thing to live with. 

I have a few, but as the song goes, too few to mention. 

Donna-Marie Manning and I are very selective about who we work with. 

Your success is our success. 

We don't have these stories to tell if you don't book. So we only want to work with committed and dedicated actors.

When you fill out this form tell us everything. 

https://form.jotform.com/253125203574248

We promise we won't laugh at you or judge you for wanting to act. 

We know people sometimes do. We don't. 

Our job is helping actors make their dreams come true. 

Don't hold back. We need to know you to coach you. 

xo KC

We have a professional stunt coordinator and stunt man and the scene involves a homeless man being set on fire.

Every safety caution will me met and we even will have a medic to evaluate all health and safety of the seton the day.

You would plan a gang of rowdy people who attack the homeless man. Great featured part and you would witness a cool live stunt and get full credits in the film and IMDb.

Due to the location being on a farm it would be preferable that you drive as public transport would be tricky.

You will be needed for maximum two hours and it pays a flat fee of ¬£30 and we can also pay your travel /fuel

 

Date is 5th of January in Bridgnorth

 

Get in touch for all info and details via PM

or email luxkapsaski@gmail.com

Vicky Boone Casting is looking for a real little league Baseball team for background roles in an Academy Sports commercial. 
Details below:

Project: Academy Sports
Production Company: The Bear
Project Type:  Social Media Campaign (will run 2 weeks)
Union Status: Non-Union
Project Rate: $250/day per family member
Shoot Date(s): January 21-23 OR 22-24, 2026 (will shoot 1 day within this range)
Shoot Location: Austin, TX. Must work local to Austin.

‚Äî
We are looking for:
[REAL LITTLE LEAGUE BASEBALL TEAM] Boys, Ages 11-12. We‚Äôre seeking a racially diverse group with natural enthusiasm and chemistry. Players should all be mid-high level skillset wise. Casting 12 players and 1-2 Coaches.

If you and your team might be a fit and are interested in submitting, please submit ASAP to submissions@vickyboonecasting.com by sending the following info:
*Name
*City you and your team are based in
*Contact Number
*Two recent photos (one of you and one of your team)
*Confirm you are avail for all the dates mentioned or list conflicts (1/21-1/23, 1/22-1/24, 2026)
*Please tell us a little bit about your team!
*Please use the subject line ‚ÄúLITTLE LEAGUE TEAM‚Äù

We look forward to your submissions!
Team VBC

items.text:
Hey Everyone,

I‚Äôm an actor based near Portland, Oregon, with four years of professional experience across film and other media. While I‚Äôm often cast in the horror genre, my training and range extend well beyond it, and I actively pursue diverse roles across multiple genres.

I trained for approximately three years primarily in the Meisner technique and continue to strengthen my craft through ongoing improv work. My projects have filmed in Los Angeles, on the East Coast, and internationally, including the feature film Irish Ashes, shot in the UK.

I‚Äôm open to a wide range of roles and characters and am fully available for both domestic and international travel.

I trained for approximately three years primarily in the Meisner technique and continue to strengthen my craft through ongoing improv work. My projects have filmed in Los Angeles, on the East Coast, and internationally, including the feature film Irish Ashes, shot in the UK.

I‚Äôm open to a wide range of roles and characters and am fully available for both domestic and international travel.

items.text:
S√∏ges: Skuespillere til kortfilm der skal optages henover sommeren 2026. Ul√∏nnet.

Da jeg g√•r med en lille vision om at bryde ud som director efter flere √•r som skuespiller i tv og film branchen. Har jeg endelig f√•et skrevet en af mine mange historier f√¶rdig, men da jeg gerne vil bryde lidt med normen s√• skiller dette projekt sig ud da det bogstaveligt er en silent montage film, sat til klassikeren "Nisi Dominus" af Vivaldi. 

Vores working title er indtil videre "The Mafia burial".
Filmen vil vare ca 20min og og vil indeholde en del slow motion og koreograferede blodige action shots. 

Kort synopsis: En respekteret Mafia boss har mistet sit et og alt, nemlig hans datter. Historien starter p√• en kirkeg√•rd hvor vi overv√¶rer hendes begravelse, med en hysterisk gr√¶dende mor, en masse s√∏rgende h√•ndlangere og mange kondolerende g√¶ster. Iblandt h√•ndlangerne st√•r vores hoved karakter. Da vi zoomer t√¶ttere p√• ham ser vi ham smide en lille t√•re, det der skiller ham ud er dog at det er mere end bare sorg vi kan se i ham, han er lige s√• knust som familien da han var datterens hemmelige elsker. Da vi zoomer mere ind p√• ham breaker vi over i hans tanker i form af en montage. Hvor vi ser ham eliminere og afh√∏re flere kriminelle i jagten p√• hans k√¶restes morder. Alt dette vil lede op til begravelsen. Der vil komme sm√• brud imellem hans voldelige handlinger hvor han sl√•r over til de sm√• gode k√¶rligheds stunder han havde med hende.

Der skildres imellem en tone af film som The Godfather og Drive. 

Da det hele basically er en silent movie s√• har vi ogs√• valgt at tage os ekstra god tid til at finde de helt rigtige skuespillere til projektet da der her udelukkende skal arbejdes med udtryk og mimik. 
Musikken som vil drive filmen vil v√¶re et mix af "Nisi Dominus" af Vivaldi samt nogle andre klassiske stykker. Det hele skydes rundt omkring i Midtjylland henover sommeren 2026, men laves til at ligne et m√∏rkt amerikansk drama. 

Dette er et komplet passion projekt s√• det hele er ul√∏nnet. Men der vil v√¶re forplejning og god stemning p√• alle set.

Action scener vil v√¶re koreograferet og vi arbejder efter et koncept hvor vi pr√∏ver at f√• s√• meget som muligt ud af s√• lidt som muligt mht til vinkler close ups and so on. 

Nogle af jer har nok set dette opslag i andre grupper og vi havde egentlig f√∏rst t√¶nkt os at begynde at caste skuespillere om en m√•neds tid. Men da rigtig mange af jer allerede har henvendt jer i h√•b om at udfylde en af de mange roller s√• kommer vores rolle liste her. 

Rolle...... (Alder)

Mafia Don, Marlon Brando vs John Turturro type(40-65)

Grieving Mafia mom, smuk sydlandsk look men skal kunne udtrykke ekstrem sorg og raseri (30-50)

Mafia Princess, sydlandsk look skal kunne udstr√•le positivt, hun er nemlig ikke som resten af hendes familie og er det eneste positive vores hovedrolle havde i sit liv (20-30)

The boyfriend, en Ryan gosling/Tom Hardy type(25-40) Hovedrollen, du skal v√¶re klar p√• at lave sm√• stunts og planlagte koreograferede fight sekvenser.

Bodyguard 1,2. Vores Mafia families personlige bodyguards kl√¶dt i sort sammen med vores hoved karakter. (30-50)

Bad guy 1,2,3,4,5 (20-40) I skal ogs√• v√¶re klar p√• at lave koreograferede fight sekvenser sammen med vores hovedrolle. 

Hitman, en fremh√¶vet bad guy der vil komme til at v√¶re m√•l for vores hovedrolles h√¶vntogt (30-50)

The other Don, en fremh√¶vet Mafia boss der sammen med sin egen familie vil v√¶re til stede under begravelsen og v√¶re fremh√¶vet som kondolerende (40-65).

Statister:

1) Der skal bruges statister under begravelsen, folk kl√¶dt i komplet sorte American style funeral outfits. 
Her skal vi bruge ca 10stk. Alder underordnet, der er dog plads til en ung statist ogs√• da vi godt kunne t√¶nke os at se et barn til stede under begravelsen, som spiller et evt familiemedlem.

2) Der skal bruges statister i baggrunden p√• nogle af vores flashbacks til vores karakterers k√¶rlighed stunder. Her skal vi bruge ca 8 personer med amerikansk hverdags look til sm√• optagelser i bla en park og evt Tivoli. 

3) Flygtende g√¶ster, n√•r vores hovedrolle konfronterer vores bad guys i en dinner, skal vi bruge ca 4 statister til at v√¶re g√¶ster i dinneren. 
Her skal man v√¶re klar p√• at f√• lidt fake blod p√• sig og evt smide lidt med tingene, da vi laver et slow motion shot der skal fange panikken i rummet. Alder og k√∏n er underordnet, men du skal kunne bev√¶ge dig hurtigt og forst√• en planlagt koreografi.

HUSK: At dette er en silent movie drevet af et klassisk soundtrack s√• derfor er det ekstra vigtigt at man kan arbejde med udtryk om mimik!

Det skal lige understreges at for at komme i betragtning til nogle af rollerne s√• SKAL ans√∏gningen sendes via email. Husk at skriv hvilken rolle i kunne v√¶re interesseret i og husk at sende opdaterede billeder for at kunne komme i betragtning. √ònsker man at medvirke som statist s√• husk at skriv om man det er gruppe 1,2 eller 3 man √∏nsker at medvirke i. Vi caster helt frem til 1.april og der vil ogs√• komme et et opslag p√• DASK hvor i kan ans√∏ge. Vi svarer kun p√• dem vi √∏nsker at bruge til projektet. S√• hvis det evt er noget for dig s√• smid en email til:

brook_lynmarvin@hotmail.com

Deadline for ans√∏gning er 1/4.2026

Pr√¶cis dato for optagelser er ikke fastlagt endnu, men holder alle vores udvalgte skuespillere og statister opdateret om forl√∏bet og projektet efterh√•nden som det skrider frem. 

Projektet laves mht til at det skal vises p√• diverse film festivaler. S√• hvis man g√•r og br√¶nder for at pr√∏ve at lave noget anderledes s√• er det her m√•ske projektet for dig.

Togetherness & Christmas... 
May it be as calm and full of warm lights as it can be.

SONGS FROM LIFE  is about togetherness. 
It plays on January 10th at 20:00 at the Gallus Theater Frankfurt.
Tickets: https://www.gallustheater.de/prog/vob.php?i=27

In February and March the show will to Adelaide and Newcastle, Australia.

sharedPost.text:
Breaking news! 

Making Contact
Two last-minute places have just come available!! 

Looking for:
One male-identifying actor
One female-identifying actor

Course sold out quickly so jump in while you have a chance. This is the only extensive actor training of its type in London.

Making Contact is a twelve-week physical theatre workshop that asks:

How do performers make contact?
How is it managed?
How do actors prepare for physical, violent and intimate scenes -  not just manage them, but take joy in the process?
How can actors break habits of hesitation and meet physical work with confidence, play and freedom?

This playful yet practical training offers a safe, yet brave space to build confidence, clarity and skill in physical connection. The work centres consent and boundary setting while encouraging curiosity, physical play and embodied listening.

Participants explore dynamic practices including gameplay, contact improvisation and shared weight work, designed to support actors in working physically with trust and enjoyment. Scenes involving intimacy, violence and imaginary relationships are approached with care, rigour and professionalism.

Led by a certified fight and intimacy director with over 30 years‚Äô international experience, Making Contact is ideal for actors who want to:
‚Äì establish clear, healthy boundaries
‚Äì move beyond hesitation around physical contact
‚Äì extend their physical range and availability
‚Äì approach intimacy and violence with confidence, care and joy

The training provides practical tools for theatre and film while fostering trust, openness and pleasure in the craft.

Participants will explore:
‚Äì industry standards in intimacy and consent
‚Äì mental and physical preparation for the work
‚Äì quality boundary setting
‚Äì physical exploration and gameplay
‚Äì contact improvisation and shared weight
‚Äì exploration of theatrical violence
‚Äì engagement in imaginary relationships under physical circumstances
‚Äì body preparation and physical / mental closure
‚Äì final performances of fully coordinated and directed scenes

üìÖ Jan 10 ‚Äì March 28, 2026
‚è± 12 weeks | In-person | London
üí∞ ¬£450 (deposit options available)

www.bodymindvoice.co.uk

items.text:
**AUDITION NOTICE**

Levity Players Group, a professional theatre company performing in Independence, Kansas City, and other locations, is auditioning talented and dedicated actors.  Our next audition opportunity is:

Sunday, January 4th, 2026 ‚Äì 1:30 p.m.

Corinth Public Library

8100 Mission Road

Prairie Village, KS 66208

 

Please be there before 1:30 p.m., as the director has remarks to share with all auditioners.  The show we are auditioning for*** ***is*** The Canine Memorial Dinner Valentine‚Äôs Murder or Now, Youse Can‚Äôt Leave!  ***This show will be performed in February.  There is also the possibility of being cast in **Murder at Miss Kitty Katty‚Äôs Cool Dude Ranch** **or** **Who let the Horses out of the Corral?**  That show will be performed in March.  There is also the possibility of being cast in ***The Real Estate Seminar Murder or A Dead Seller Is a Motivated Seller****.  That show will be performed in April.*  In summary, this is an opportunity to secure three months of acting work by auditioning once. 

We present fully interactive, family-friendly murder mystery comedies.  Our covenant with our audiences and with our venue partners is that our shows will not contain objectionable language or situations.

Please bring headshots and resumes if you have them.  Auditions will consist of cold readings of sides.  No monologues will be needed.

This is absolutely a paid professional acting opportunity.  Pay is fifty dollars per show plus tips earned from serving guests dinner and drinks.  Tips have ranged from a low of approximately thirty dollars per show to a high of one hundred dollars per show.  In addition, the director may pay bonuses at the end of the run predicated upon an actor‚Äôs contribution to the team.  This is the number one paying professional theatre performance job in greater Kansas City on a dollar per hour invested basis.

We hope to meet you at the auditions.  If you have questions that need to be answered prior to the auditions, please feel free to telephone the company Artistic Director (Greg) at 314-456-3978.

üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äì STUDENT SHORT FILM üé¨

**UNPAID**

Hey everyone! I‚Äôm currently casting for my upcoming short film, *After the Rain*, an intimate emotional drama about two sisters navigating the aftermath of their mother‚Äôs sudden death. When a violent storm forces Mia and Isla back together, unspoken grief and buried pain rise to the surface, pushing them toward understanding, healing, and renewed connection.

To be shot in: High Wycombe/ London 

**Synopsis:**

After their mother‚Äôs sudden death, two sisters are pulled apart by grief, distance, and unspoken pain. Mia, the older sister, leaves to pursue a promising job opportunity, trying to outrun the heartbreak of their loss. Isla stays behind, sinking into isolation and self-destructive behaviour as her distress deepens. When Mia returns on a stormy night to find Isla drunk and unravelling, the sisters are forced to confront years of buried resentment and abandonment. Through raw confessions and shared vulnerability, they begin a journey towards understanding, forgiveness, and the possibility of hope, finding solace in the quiet strength of sisterhood. 

Characters:

**ISLA (19-22, FEMALE)** 

impulsive, reckless, emotionally unstable little sister. Must be able to portray internal conflict and intoxication.  

**MIA (25-28, FEMALE)**

protective, compassionate, responsible older sister. Must be able to portray internal conflict and the effects of grief. 

Shooting: DATES TBC  (approx JAN 6-16th)    

If interested, please contact me for more information at austenfilmworks@gmail.com 

Please feel free to share or tag anyone who might be interested. üé•üé¨

items.text:
S√∏ges: Cinematographer/kameramand til kortfilm der skal optages henover sommeren 2026. Ul√∏nnet.

Da jeg g√•r med en lille vision om at bryde ud som director efter flere √•r som skuespiller i tv og film branchen. Har jeg endelig f√•et skrevet en af mine mange historier f√¶rdig, men da jeg gerne vil bryde lidt med normen s√• skiller dette projekt sig ud da det bogstaveligt er en silent montage film, sat til klassikeren "Nisi Dominus" af Vivaldi. 

Vores working title er indtil videre "The Mafia burial".
Filmen vil vare ca 20min og og vil indeholde en del slow motion og koreograferede blodige action shots. 

Kort synopsis: En respekteret Mafia boss har mistet sit et og alt, nemlig hans datter. Historien starter p√• en kirkeg√•rd hvor vi overv√¶rer hendes begravelse, med en hysterisk gr√¶dende mor, en masse s√∏rgende h√•ndlangere og mange kondolerende g√¶ster. Iblandt h√•ndlangerne st√•r vores hoved karakter. Da vi zoomer t√¶ttere p√• ham ser vi ham smide en lille t√•re, det der skiller ham ud er dog at det er mere en bare sorg vi kan se i ham, han er lige s√• knust som familien da han var datterens hemmelige elsker. Da vi zoomer mere ind p√• ham breaker vi over i hans tanker i form af en montage. Hvor vi ser ham eliminere og afh√∏re flere kriminelle i jagten p√• hans k√¶restes morder. Alt dette vil lede op til begravelsen. Der vil komme sm√• brud imellem hans voldelige handlinger hvor han sl√•r over til de sm√• gode k√¶rligheds stunder han havde med hende.

Der skildres imellem en tone af film som The Godfather og Drive. 

Da det hele basically er en silent movie s√• har vi ogs√• valgt at tage os ekstra god tid til at finde de helt rigtige skuespillere til projektet da der her udelukkende skal arbejdes med udtryk og mimik. 
Musikken som vil drive filmen vil v√¶re et mix af "Nisi Dominus" af Vivaldi samt nogle andre klassiske stykker. Det hele skydes rundt omkring i Midtjylland men laves til at ligne et m√∏rkt amerikansk drama. 

Dette er et komplet passion projekt s√• det hele er ul√∏nnet. Men der vil v√¶re forplejning og god stemning p√• alle set.

Action scener vil v√¶re koreograferet og vi arbejder efter et koncept hvor vi pr√∏ver at f√• s√• meget som muligt ud af s√• lidt som muligt mht til vinkler close ups and so on. 

Vi begynder f√∏rst at kigge efter skuespillere n√•r det rigtige crew er fundet. Men skulle man falde over det her og t√¶nke at det er lige noget for mig s√• er man mere end velkommen til at skrive til os. 
Men i f√∏rste omgang ledes der efter en kameramand der selv har det n√∏dvendige udstyr og som kan se vores vision. Gerne med henblik p√• et fremtidigt samarbejde til flere produktioner i fremtiden. S√• hvis det evt er dig s√• smid en email til:

brook_lynmarvin@hotmail.com

Deadline for ans√∏gning er 1/3.2026

Projektet laves mht til at det skal vises p√• diverse film festivaler. S√• hvis man g√•r og br√¶nder for optagelse og editing og har lyst til at pr√∏ve at lave noget anderledes s√• er det her m√•ske projektet for dig.

items.text:
**CASTINGOPSLAG ‚Äì KORTFILM ‚ÄúALT I INTET‚Äù**

Vi s√∏ger **skuespillere i alderen 18‚Äì23 √•r** til hovedrollerne i vores kommende **ul√∏nnede kortfilm** *Alt I Intet*.
**Forplejning vil v√¶re inkluderet under optagelserne.**
Projektet har ambitioner om festivaldeltagelse og √∏nsker at skabe et v√¶rk, der kan n√• ud til et bredere publikum.

**Om projektet**

*‚ÄùAlt I Intet‚Äù* er et karakterdrevet drama, der unders√∏ger temaer som k√¶rlighed, sorg og identitet. Filmen bev√¶ger sig i gr√¶nselandet mellem virkelighed og erindring og skildrer en ung mands indre rejse efter et stort tab.

**Om os**

Vi er tre unge filmskabere med en f√¶lles passion for at skabe st√¶rke fort√¶llinger og ambiti√∏se filmiske v√¶rker med fokus p√• stemning, f√∏lelser og karakterudvikling.

 

**Roller**

**Oliver (mand, 18‚Äì23 √•r)**
Oliver er en ung, f√∏lsom og reflekterende mand, der er dybt knyttet til sine relationer. Udadtil fremst√•r han stille og n√¶sten anonym, som om han bev√¶ger sig gennem hverdagen p√• autopilot. Han lever prim√¶rt i minderne om sin afd√∏de k√¶reste, som fortsat p√•virker hans hverdag og selvforst√•else.

**Emma (kvinde, 18‚Äì23 √•r)**
Emma er en varm, n√¶rv√¶rende og livlig ung kvinde, der form√•r at se Oliver, n√•r han ikke selv kan. Hun repr√¶senterer b√•de k√¶rlighed, tryghed og det liv, Oliver har mistet.

 

**Logline**

Fortabt i minderne om Emma genoplever Oliver sit tab p√• gr√¶nsen mellem virkelighed og hallucinationer, indtil et m√∏de mellem liv og d√∏d giver ham et nyt blik p√• sig selv ‚Äì og p√• det liv, der stadig venter.

 

**Optagedatoer**

**L√∏rdag d. 7. marts ‚Äì s√∏ndag d. 8. marts**

**L√∏rdag d. 14. marts ‚Äì s√∏ndag d. 15. marts**

 

**Vigtig information**

Da filmen behandler temaer som k√¶rlighed og sorg, vil der indg√• semi-intime scener, herunder kram, h√•ndholdning og t√¶t fysisk kontakt.

For den kvindelige rolle forekommer der enkelte scener i badet√∏j. Disse scener har ingen seksuel karakter og vil blive behandlet med respekt og tydelig kommunikation.

 

**Ans√∏gning**

Vi ser gerne, at interesserede sender f√∏lgende:

**Selftape**

**Portr√¶tbillede**

**Alder og h√∏jde**

Ans√∏gning og eventuelle sp√∏rgsm√•l kan sendes via:
**E-mail:** magn715c@gmail.com
**Messenger: **Undertegnet

Vi ser frem til at h√∏re fra jer.

 

**Venlig hilsen**
**Magnus Petersen**
Producer ‚Äì ‚Äù*Alt I Intet‚Äù*

And I have reduced the price of the whole course for December for all your gifting (or self gifting) needs! 

Beat the January blues by having a wonderful group of performers to enjoy acting with, or give someone that boost into performance they keep talking about doing.

items.text:
We are looking for an interested producer to film our comedy Movie "Valley Boys Return" and Our drama movie "Wilbur Street Gangs" and our sitcom "So, You Want to Prank Me, Huh?" Our Valley Boys Return movie is a very funny comical movie about me and my friend growing up in Southern California in the 1970s and 1980s and the very funny comical experience we had happen to us. I believe this comedy movie will be a huge success and we know with everything that has happened in the last five or so years, people need a comical movie to laugh. The other proposals are, "So, You want to Prank me, Huh?" Another funny sitcom show that we would write different shows for it weekly. And the other movie proposal is titled, "The Wilbur Street Gangs" which is more of a drama about my friend and I growing-up in Southern California and the start of the gangs that frequented Southern California and the San Fernando Valley.

We are looking for a producer that will handle the filming of our two movies and sitcom television show, handle working as a team to find funding, (angel investors, etc.) and after our movie is filmed and television shows, get them to Hollywood to make it to the big screen. We will work as a team with our producer on playing parts in our movies and show and consult on set as you are filming and work with our producers team to get our script completely written to turn our movie and shows into Hollywood hits.

We can also work with our interested producer to find investors, angel investors, etc to fund the filming of our two movies and television show if the producer does not have the funding available. The producer should have points of contact they have worked with in the past for funding sources.

Or, if an interested producer wants to buy our movie ideas and sitcom show ideas, we can negotiate a price to sell them to our interested producer.

If you are interested in learning more about our movies and television show, respond back to this Facebook post or Email be directly at (ronanselm35@gmail.com) and we can set-up a time to talk about where I will go over our movies in more detail and our television show. I have all the proposals written for the movies and shows and a very rough draft script written for the "Valley Boys Return" movie which we would like to sit down with your team and finish the script as a team. Send me a good contact email for you and I can send you a copy of each of our proposals if you are interested.

Though she 1S absent in the present timeline, her relationships and unresolved secrets drive the emotional core of the story. Actor must convey depth, vulnerability, and subtle foreshadowing.'

May be an image of text that says 'SAM (Teen, any ethnicity) Popular and outwardly confident, SSam is well-liked and admired at school, but beneath the surface she 1S genuinely kind and empathetic. She struggles with guilt and unspoken tension connected to Eliana's disappearance. Sam often feels caught between maintaining her image and confronting difficult truths. üé≠ CASTING CALL üé≠
Mr Poole (and The Father)
 in "Dr Jekyll and Mr Hyde"
Grove Productions

We‚Äôre seeking an actor to join our touring production as Mr Poole, Dr Jekyll‚Äôs long-serving butler, who witnesses his master‚Äôs terrifying descent. This is a key supporting role with strong emotional scenes. The role also includes a small secondary part, The Father.

‚ú® Blind casting ‚Äì all actors welcome
üó£Ô∏è Working-class / regional accent required

üíº Pay
‚Ä¢ ¬£101 per performance (inc. holiday pay)
‚Ä¢ ¬£15 per hour for rehearsals (inc. holiday pay)

‚ö†Ô∏è Mid-run replacement ‚Äì fast learning essential
üé≠ Small rep company ‚Äì cast help move props/set & assist with get-outs
‚ôø Reasonable adjustments available

üìÖ Auditions: 9 January
üìÖ Rehearsals: 15 & 16 January

üéüÔ∏è Performance Dates:
‚Ä¢ 19 Jan ‚Äì Clevedon School (Bristol)
‚Ä¢ 3 Feb ‚Äì The Crypt (Gloucester)
‚Ä¢ 9/10 Feb (TBC) ‚Äì Hodge Hill (Birmingham)
‚Ä¢ 9 March ‚Äì Blakehay Theatre, Weston-super-Mare
‚Ä¢ 12 March ‚Äì Blakehay Theatre, Weston-super-Mare
‚Ä¢ 16 March ‚Äì Cheltenham Ladies‚Äô College

üì© To apply:
Send your CV + video audition (using the provided Poole extract) to
admin@groveproductions.org
Closing date for application: 5pm 6th January

Poole Extract

Context - Poole has become increasingly concerned about his master, Dr Jekyll, and has gone to Jekyll‚Äôs friend, Utterson, for help. In this scene, Poole has just asked Utterson to listen at the door to his master‚Äôs voice, as Poole believes it is not his master but a different man, or monster.

Poole:
Well, Mr Utterson, you are a hard man to satisfy. But I‚Äôll do it yet. All this last week, he or it or whatever it is that lives in the laboratory, has been crying night and day for some sort of medicine and cannot get it to his mind. It was sometimes his way ‚Äì the master‚Äôs that is ‚Äì to write his orders on a sheet of paper and throw it on the stair. We‚Äôve had nothing else this week back. Nothing but papers, and a closed door, and the very meals left there to be smuggled in when nobody was looking. Well sir, every day, ay, and twice and thrice in the same day, there have been orders and complaints, and I have been sent flying to all the wholesale chemists in town. Every time I brought the stuff back, there would be another paper telling me to return it, because it was not pure, and another order to a different firm. This drug is wanted bitter bad, sir, whatever for.

DM for more info

‚ú® Grounded realism

üì© Submit to Klattstudioscasting@gmail.com

üèîÔ∏è CASTING: MOTHER CARTER

The quiet heart of a secluded mountain home offering refuge‚Äîand concern.

‚ú® Subtle, expressive acting

‚ú® Strong presence with minimal dialogue

üì© Submit to Klattstudioscasting@gmail.com

Subject: Kiara‚Äôs Psalm ‚Äì Mother Carter

‚ö†Ô∏è Dark, nuanced character

K-latt Studios

sharedPost.text:
I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies and some kind of Art House Underground Movies. I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.

I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch

Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928

Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 

please ask for details.

message.text:
Here‚Äôs a quote from Elia Kazan:

‚ÄúNo one can teach anyone to Act. An existing talent is only made stronger and clearer and smarter. 

A good actor is intelligent in a rustic, basic, almost feral way: He or she has been observing people in various behaviors for a lifetime, noticing how they operate, how they think, how they take in information. Almost all good actors are recessive, shy. In an audition or a meeting, you can see the way their eyes move and their hands work, and you instantly recognize the child they were and the artist they‚Äôre becoming. They are always studying, taking things in.‚Äù

The best performances‚Äîof all artists‚Äîhave been loved into existence.‚Äù

~~ director ELIA KAZAN 

IN PERSON OR ONLINE COACHING with Michael Caruana at bongo productions. 

Sign up for any of the 3 steps our comprehensive CERTIFICATE PROGRAM! 

STEP 1: PRIVATE COACHING - 6x1hr sessions, learn or re-enforce the essentials, with trusted analysis techniques and direction, we go deep. We prepare and tape four contrasting monologues. 

STEP 2: SEMIPRIVATE, SCENE-STUDY, OPTION 2: 3x2hr sessions. I partner you, we review and apply the preparation techniques from Step 1. We tape 2 scenes with playback, notes and direction, with a focus on on-camera technique - living the scene! Add to your reel! 

STEP 2, 2nd OPTION: Thursday night SCENE STUDY CLASS A challenging and inspirational class applying fundamental analysis to compelling scenes. Each actor prepares and tapes 2 scenes, with coaching and using 2 cameras. Perfect for beginners to build a stable foundation and working professionals to sharpen acting tools, with a playful vibe. THURSDAYS - 6-9 pm üé¨

STEP 3: THE SUCCESSFUL AUDITIONS WORKSHOP - 2 days, all about auditioning plus SELF-TAPE AUDITIONS, for commercials and film and TV series, we tape your 2 auditions, with critique, coaching, direction and demonstration. Repeats every 3rd month at bongo productions.

Professional coaching, with Michael Caruana, at bongo productions, trusted since 1996! 

For more contact Michael at:
416 294-3754 or visit: 

bongoproductions.com
